      "description": "No Full Name Given: Mack is presumably a nickname but we never learn what it's short for, or whether it's a shortening of his first or last name. Unintelligible Accent: He's got a thick Glaswegian accent and the Brockmans struggle to understand him. Karen even asks him what language he's speaking. Also played with when he walks into the kitchen and says \"Happy Christmas\" in Gaelic, much to everyone's confusion. Funny Foreigner: He basically exists to play this role, for example thinking that Boris Johnson is a comedy character rather than a real person. Germanic Depressives: He's a stereotypical German with a serious demeanour.",
